history.content: Have you tried talking to Cindy Connors, the CS Enrollment Manager, about this? cs-enrollments@cs.berkeley.edu

Hello,

I recently took CS61A during this past fall semester, and unfortunately I was not able to pass the class. When I went to re-register for the class again, it did indicate that there were spots open, however I was not able to register because the system detected a conflict because I had already taken the class, and it automatically put me on the waitlist. I am confused as I now am 165 on the waitlist despite me attempting to register for the class when there were available spots open.

Now that the semester is close to starting, I am still seeing myself on the waitlist for the class. Are there any chances of the class expanding? I did talk to my instructor, and he mentioned posting here to see if there is anyone that can help me enroll in the class, given that it was a system conflict that caused me to not be able to enroll.

Please let me know what the next steps are.
history.subject: CS 61A expanding?
